 &quot;Thank you Hera.&quot; she said softly. She turned back and sat down once more by the fire. <br>
 Solari managed to rest a bit before those who were sent out to get the information were due back. The pain in her body was subsiding, not that a little pain was going to stop Solari anyway. She thought about what had been discussed with Hera and prayed that Hippolyta was holding out. She was really going to make the Roman that took her suffer. Solari was going to kill him herself, but she thought about it further and decided that he needed to have a dose of his own medicine and therefore, she was going to take him captive, so everyone could relish in a kill.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#993300>(4/21/03 10:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=169>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: tests</span><hr size=1> Alysia growled as she could hear the men shouting. She turned her eyes downward and saw Scythe in a fight with one of their dogs. She yelled, &quot;Scythe, what are you doing!?&quot;<br>
<br>
Scythe growled as it continued fighting.<br>
