<br>
She looked to Arixa.<br>
<br>
&quot;When you get my signal, call the others to one by one pick off the guards that come near that tent. Whoever is inside with Hippolyte won't notice his men are missing since he appears to be keeping himself busy with our athelfi. Then, get back to the village and tell Odessa to let Solari know what we know now.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alysia's bright eyes turned back as the Roman came close. The other men were gathered around a small campfire. A few of them were off scouting the woods, and without their knowledge, each was followed closely by a wolf.<br>
As he came within leaping distance, Alysia barked, &quot;Go Arixa.&quot; At which Arixa left into the woods giving soft barking sounds that the Scynthian wolves could hear and obey. The young wolf turned back to see Alysia.<br>
<br>
Alysia grinned deviously as she jumped towards the Roman, and giving him no chance to scream, her teeth instantly sunk into his throat tackling him to the ground.<br>
<br>
~~~<br>
<br>
Arixa dashed into the camp and came swiftly to Odessa nudging her leg. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 867<br> <font color=#993300>(4/25/03 9:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=175>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prey and Predator</span><hr size=1> The romans fought off the few wolves that could see, cursing the one who killed one of their dogs.  Meanwhile, their leader believed there was more to this than it seemed.  Standing at the door of his hut with one of his men, he watched as finally the village woke up and began to properly defend itself.  Then he nodded to his friend and walked back into the hut.<br>
<br>
Walking inside, he walked up to Hippolyte.  &quot;Tell me about the wolves outside.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hippolyte's eyes showed no emotion.  But, when he mentioned the wolves she knew that the Scythians were there.  She had heard the sound of the wolves and then the dog fighting.  But, she could not be sure....now she was.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Tell me slave..what is it with the wolves outside.  They are not normal wolves are they?&quot;<br>
<br>
Still, Hippolyte showed no emotion nor spoke any word.  <br>
<br>
Her captor just laughed and then got a wicked grin.  &quot;You don't have to tell me anything.&quot;  He untied her and grabbed the ropes that held her wrists together. And then pushed her towards the door.  &quot;We will see what these wolves are for.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kicking the door open, he then shoved Hippolyte forward and then yanked her back.  Standing behind her, he quickly pressed a dagger into the side of her throat.  Pressing so hard that a small droplet of blood began to seep.  &quot;Wolves, I suggest that you leave now...or this ...beast dies.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Beast?  Had Hippolyte heard him right.  Was her captor beginning to believe the myths of the beast women of the forests? <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

